1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the diversity multiplexing tradeoff performance of a relay network, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a distributed D-BLAST architecture for the relay network, which is a networking and internet architecture topic. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses a space-time coding strategy for the relay network, which is a systems and control topic. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the transmission of data in a relay network, which is a multimedia topic. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may touch on the societal implications of improving wireless relay networks.
